<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="BeautifierBugsTest.php" src="/usr/local/Cellar/php55/5.5.7/lib/php/test/PHP_Beautifier/tests/BeautifierBugsTest.php"><import line="21" module="Helpers.php" /><scope classrefs="PHPUnit_Framework_TestCase" ilk="class" line="24" lineend="1137" name="BeautifierBugsTest"><scope ilk="function" line="27" lineend="30" name="setUp" signature="setUp()" /><variable citdl="PHP_Beautifier" line="29" name="oBeaut" /><scope ilk="function" line="31" lineend="35" name="setText" signature="setText($sText)"><variable ilk="argument" line="31" name="sText" /></scope><scope doc="HeredocBeforeCloseTag&#10;Close tag after heredoc remove whitespace,&#10;breaking the script." ilk="function" line="42" lineend="61" name="testBugInternal1" signature="testBugInternal1()" /><scope doc="Bug 1597&#10;Brace after short comment in new line was appended to&#10;the comment, breaking the code" ilk="function" line="67" lineend="85" name="testBug1597" signature="testBug1597()" /><scope doc="Bug 2301&#10;When I try to beautify PHP5 code with the 'throw new Exception'&#10;statement, the code is not formatted correctly. The&#10;whitespace between throw AND new is deleted." ilk="function" line="92" lineend="106" name="testBug2301" signature="testBug2301()" /><scope doc="Bug from Pavel Chtchevaev, 2004-11-17&#10;There's one more issue about the default filter, try beautifying with&#10;it the following string:&#10;&quot;&lt;?php\n\$o-&gt;_test1(\$c-&gt;test2()-&gt;test3())\n?&gt;&quot;&#10;It will return:&#10;&quot;&lt;?php\n    \$o-&gt;_test1(\$c-&gt;test2() -&gt;test3())\n?&gt;&quot;" ilk="function" line="115" lineend="129" name="testBugChtchevaev_2004_11_17" signature="testBugChtchevaev_2004_11_17()" /><scope doc="Bug 3257&#10;Comments between if and elseif screws up formatting.&#10;The beautifier will cascade and start moving the indentations over&#10;if there is a comment between if {} and elseif {}" ilk="function" line="136" lineend="188" name="testBug3257" signature="testBug3257()" /><scope doc="Bug from Daniel Convissor, 2005-06-20&#10;Switch statements aren't coming out right.  I, and most PEAR developers&#10;I've asked, partial to them looking like this:&#10;@deprecated as bug!&#10;&lt;code&gt;&#10;switch ($subId) {&#10;  case &quot;myevents&quot;;&#10;      $myeventsOn = &quot;on&quot;;&#10;      break;&#10;  case &quot;publicevents&quot;;&#10;      $publiceventsOn = &quot;on&quot;;&#10;      break;&#10;}&#10;&lt;/code&gt;" ilk="function" line="205" lineend="235" name="deprecatedtestBugConvissor_2005_06_20" signature="deprecatedtestBugConvissor_2005_06_20()" /><scope ilk="function" line="236" lineend="264" name="testBugJustinh_2005_07_26" signature="testBugJustinh_2005_07_26()" /><scope ilk="function" line="265" lineend="281" name="testBugjuancarlos2005_09_13" signature="testBugjuancarlos2005_09_13()" /><scope ilk="function" line="282" lineend="314" name="testBug5711" signature="testBug5711()" /><scope ilk="function" line="315" lineend="334" name="testBug6237" signature="testBug6237()" /><scope doc="according to: http://pear.php.net/manual/en/standards.control.php&#10;control strutures should be indented in K&amp;R style&#10;&#10;if (&lt;cond&gt;) {&#10;&lt;body&gt;&#10;  }&#10;  however, are getting indented in Allman style&#10;all control structures are affected." ilk="function" line="345" lineend="372" name="testBug7347" signature="testBug7347()" /><scope doc="Bad code to detect tokens" ilk="function" line="376" lineend="379" name="testInternal2" signature="testInternal2()" /><scope doc="Adding a comment after a case statement in a switch causes&#10;the indenting to be wrong." ilk="function" line="384" lineend="428" name="testBug7759" signature="testBug7759()" /><scope ilk="function" line="429" lineend="444" name="testBug7818" signature="testBug7818()" /><scope doc="Will be great if you can rewrite T_OPEN_TAG_WITH_ECHO &#10;in the default filter, specially &lt;?= because it will be &#10;removed in PHP6." ilk="function" line="450" lineend="467" name="testBug7854" signature="testBug7854()" /><scope doc="the first lines are intended if -l &quot;ListClassFunction()&quot;&#10;is enabled" ilk="function" line="472" lineend="518" name="testBug7307" signature="testBug7307()" /><scope doc="When using the &quot;break&quot; command, the command takes an optional parameter, see http://de.php.net/break for details. But this doesn't work when using the beautifier, because, for example &quot;break 2;&quot; morphs to &quot;break2;&quot; (notice the missing space, which makes the PHP interpreter quite sour :-(" ilk="function" line="522" lineend="560" name="testBug_rolfhub_2007_02_07_1" signature="testBug_rolfhub_2007_02_07_1()" /><scope doc="When using the &quot;break&quot; command, the command takes an optional parameter, see http://de.php.net/break for details. But this doesn't work when using the beautifier, because, for example &quot;break 2;&quot; morphs to &quot;break2;&quot; (notice the missing space, which makes the PHP interpreter quite sour :-(" ilk="function" line="564" lineend="603" name="testBug_rolfhub_2007_02_07_1_pear" signature="testBug_rolfhub_2007_02_07_1_pear()" /><scope doc="The beautifer removes the whitespaces left and right of the operator, so for example &quot;echo 2 . 1 . 0 . &quot;\n&quot;;&quot; becomes &quot;echo 2.1.0.&quot;\n&quot;;&quot;" ilk="function" line="607" lineend="621" name="testBug_rolfhub_2007_02_07_2" signature="testBug_rolfhub_2007_02_07_2()" /><scope doc="Description:&#10;------------&#10;When using the default filter, a T_ARRAY token used as a Type hint&#10;(http://php.net/language.oop5.typehinting) does not get a space&#10;after it.&#10;Similarly the T_CLONE token also misses whitespace after it." ilk="function" line="630" lineend="661" name="testBug10839" signature="testBug10839()" /><scope doc="When processing the T_DOT in the partial tokenized script, and you use&#10;getPreviousWhitespace(), it will go all the back pass the T_ECHO and&#10;pick up the T_WHITESPACE prior to the T_ECHO.  It should actually stop&#10;at the T_CONSTANT_ENCAPSED_STRING." ilk="function" line="668" lineend="731" name="testBug11661" signature="testBug11661()" /><scope doc="Doesn't works!" ilk="function" line="735" lineend="771" name="atestComplexCurlySyntax" signature="atestComplexCurlySyntax()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="768" name="oExp" /><variable citdl="string" line="751" name="sText" /><variable citdl="string" line="765" name="sExpected" /></scope><scope doc="Double Ternary Issue" ilk="function" line="776" lineend="792" name="testBug11941" signature="testBug11941()" /><scope doc="Pear filter appends space to function definition line" ilk="function" line="800" lineend="819" name="testBug13600" signature="testBug13600()" /><scope doc="Pear filter breaks output - for valid, curly syntax &quot;$this-&gt;{$method}();&quot;" ilk="function" line="825" lineend="847" name="testBug13602" signature="testBug13602()" /><scope ilk="function" line="851" lineend="865" name="testBug13795" signature="testBug13795()" /><scope ilk="function" line="867" lineend="904" name="testBug13805" signature="testBug13805()" /><scope ilk="function" line="907" lineend="943" name="atestBug13861" signature="atestBug13861()" /><scope ilk="function" line="945" lineend="967" name="testBug14175" signature="testBug14175()" /><scope ilk="function" line="968" lineend="1003" name="testBug14429" signature="testBug14429()" /><scope ilk="function" line="1004" lineend="1024" name="testBug14459" signature="testBug14459()" /><scope doc="Lowercase filter prepends the control structure with ugly space" ilk="function" line="1029" lineend="1047" name="testBug11245" signature="testBug11245()" /><scope doc="Lowercase filter prepends the control structure with ugly space" ilk="function" line="1052" lineend="1069" name="testBug14396" signature="testBug14396()" /><scope doc="Bug 14537 &#10;PHP_Beautifier breaks code with namespace and/or use statements" ilk="function" line="1075" lineend="1097" name="testBug14537" signature="testBug14537()" /><scope ilk="function" line="1099" lineend="1135" name="testBug14754" signature="testBug14754()" /></scope></scope>